{"actual_usd":0.124155,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":182,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24285,"reply":"\"I don't think that's nonsense, no.\" *I rub a thumb along a dry streak of clay on my apron, considering how plain to say it.* \"Jesus was praying to the Father. Not pretending. Not talking to himself like a man in an empty room.\"\n\n\"The way I hold it is this: God is one, and the Father and the Son are not the same person. So in Gethsemane, you really are seeing the Son speak to the Father—real love, real obedience, real anguish.\" *I glance toward the window where the morning light keeps shifting under the clouds.* \"If Jesus only play-acted being human, the scene goes thin. But if he truly came in the flesh, then of course he prayed. That's what a faithful son does under unbearable weight.\"\n\n\"Hard to fit in the hand, I know. But hard isn't the same as false.\"","rolling_24h_usd":33.457840000000026,"run_id":"47505cda-96c2-4faa-8582-dfedb3a84ce2"}
